Come on, let's go.

549
00:45:50,030 --> 00:45:52,370
-Loser buys drinks, okay?
-Okay. Let's go.

550
00:45:52,450 --> 00:45:54,080
Hey, let me join, let me join.

551
00:46:28,280 --> 00:46:29,950
I wanna say I'm sorry.

552
00:46:40,170 --> 00:46:41,670
I went to where In-han is.

553
00:46:42,750 --> 00:46:44,750
You went to see my brother?

554
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:46,710
So, uh, just so you know,

555
00:46:48,050 --> 00:46:49,880
while I didn't directly cause
what happened,

556
00:46:49,970 --> 00:46:52,430
it is true the guys
were bullying him that day.

557
00:46:54,560 --> 00:46:56,010
And it's all my fault.

558
00:46:58,600 --> 00:47:00,980
I should've stepped in
and put a stop to it all.

559
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:07,820
At the time, I just couldn't stand
seeing him hang out with Jae-i.

560
00:47:08,320 --> 00:47:09,860
So I just stood there

561
00:47:09,950 --> 00:47:12,320
as they tormented him
and pushed him around.

562
00:47:16,580 --> 00:47:17,620
Look, I know

563
00:47:18,750 --> 00:47:20,500
I'll probably never be forgiven.

564
00:47:22,170 --> 00:47:23,130
Even so…

565
00:47:26,630 --> 00:47:27,840
I owe an apology

566
00:47:29,840 --> 00:47:31,720
both to you and to…

567
00:47:33,010 --> 00:47:34,220
and to In-han too.

568
00:47:35,930 --> 00:47:37,350
I lost my brother, Ri-an.

569
00:47:39,060 --> 00:47:42,640
You could apologize a million times,
and still, it won't bring him back.

570
00:47:45,310 --> 00:47:46,520
You're sorry, are you?

571
00:47:53,070 --> 00:47:54,160
Must be nice.

572
00:47:58,580 --> 00:48:00,450
If it wasn't for that accident,

573
00:48:02,210 --> 00:48:05,250
my brother would still be here,
laughing and joking with me.

574
00:48:06,500 --> 00:48:08,250
If you guys didn't bully him,

575
00:48:09,090 --> 00:48:11,550
if he wasn't driven
into the streets so late…

576
00:48:13,550 --> 00:48:14,470
then he'd…

577
00:48:16,390 --> 00:48:18,060
he'd still be alive and well.

578
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:24,350
You're sorry?

579
00:48:25,100 --> 00:48:26,020
All right.

580
00:48:27,310 --> 00:48:28,190
Just

581
00:48:29,070 --> 00:48:31,190
take that guilt and learn to live with it.

582
00:48:33,570 --> 00:48:34,950
Because I will never

583
00:48:36,240 --> 00:48:37,660
accept your apology.

584
00:48:52,170 --> 00:48:54,760
Everything is a result
of my negligence.

585
00:48:55,300 --> 00:48:58,800
Before being the chairperson
and the leader of a group,

586
00:48:58,890 --> 00:49:02,270
I am a mother,
and my child has caused trouble.

587
00:49:03,810 --> 00:49:05,600
And for that, I apologize.

588
00:49:05,690 --> 00:49:08,230
However, the illegal video
currently circulating

589
00:49:08,310 --> 00:49:10,110
is a clear violation of the law.

590
00:49:10,190 --> 00:49:13,030
We will take legal actions
to curtail its circulation.

591
00:49:13,610 --> 00:49:15,150
Mr. Choi Yun-seok.

592
00:49:15,240 --> 00:49:17,280
Do you admit
to inflicting acts of violence

593
00:49:17,360 --> 00:49:18,950
on the scholarship students?

594
00:49:20,080 --> 00:49:21,330
And lastly,

595
00:49:21,410 --> 00:49:25,660
I fully acknowledge the magnitude
of the violence and inappropriate behavior

596
00:49:25,750 --> 00:49:29,000
by the students
of Jooshin's private institution,

597
00:49:29,080 --> 00:49:32,460
and I vow to ensure
all wrongs shall be righted.

598
00:49:32,550 --> 00:49:34,510
Choi Yun-seok, Baek Chan-min,

599
00:49:34,590 --> 00:49:36,630
Kwon Jae-jun, Cha Ji-seok, Lee Yu-jin.

600
00:49:36,720 --> 00:49:38,680
Do you still deny your actions?

601
00:49:51,650 --> 00:49:52,610
I am also

602
00:49:53,820 --> 00:49:54,780
an offender.

603
00:50:08,040 --> 00:50:09,920
Maybe I should've just come clean

604
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:11,960
about visiting Jae-i's father.

605
00:50:12,040 --> 00:50:14,340
You already destroyed
your dad's presidential campaign

606
00:50:14,420 --> 00:50:16,010
by handing over that spy pen.

607
00:50:18,340 --> 00:50:22,430
And you know there are times
when some things are better left unsaid.

608
00:50:23,510 --> 00:50:25,020
Like your betrayal of Jae-i.

609
00:50:25,100 --> 00:50:26,980
We'll be taking that to the grave,
all right?

610
00:50:28,140 --> 00:50:31,520
Just be sure to treat Jae-i and Ri-an well
till the day you die.

611
00:50:32,110 --> 00:50:33,110
Wonder if it'll change.

612
00:50:33,730 --> 00:50:34,570
What?

613
00:50:34,650 --> 00:50:35,530
Jooshin.

614
00:50:36,190 --> 00:50:37,070
Us four.

615
00:50:40,200 --> 00:50:44,620
I mean, I just don't see…
any quick fix for things like that.

616
00:50:46,200 --> 00:50:48,000
Whether that's us or Jooshin.

617
00:50:50,870 --> 00:50:51,750
I'll see you later?

618
00:50:57,460 --> 00:50:59,380
Don't go anywhere, and head straight home.

619
00:50:59,470 --> 00:51:00,840
Yeah.

620
00:51:11,230 --> 00:51:13,150
Our first time taking the bus together

621
00:51:14,690 --> 00:51:15,860
as high schoolers.

622
00:51:19,690 --> 00:51:22,320
We always took it together
in the middle school days.

623
00:51:25,620 --> 00:51:26,700
I was scared.

624
00:51:29,160 --> 00:51:30,870
And I'm sorry for avoiding you.

625
00:51:31,870 --> 00:51:33,460
I should've been there for you.

626
00:51:34,040 --> 00:51:34,920
What?

627
00:51:35,880 --> 00:51:37,920
You've changed so much
since you've become rich.

628
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:40,380
When did we ever
apologize for stuff like that?

629
00:51:40,920 --> 00:51:43,390
We would beat each other up
and just let it slide.

630
00:51:44,340 --> 00:51:46,810
Don't you remember?
In-han would always go,

631
00:51:46,890 --> 00:51:48,390
"That stuff happens between friends."

632
00:52:01,110 --> 00:52:03,740
See now? Told you it'd look good on you.

633
00:52:03,820 --> 00:52:06,030
Yeah, but that's a given.

634
00:52:06,120 --> 00:52:07,160
I'm Yoon He-ra.

635
00:52:09,200 --> 00:52:10,040
He-ra.

636
00:52:10,870 --> 00:52:11,750
Mm-hmm?

637
00:52:12,460 --> 00:52:15,710
I never knew
that you secretly felt that way.

638
00:52:16,500 --> 00:52:19,250
I know that I can be direct
and a bit cold.

639
00:52:20,710 --> 00:52:24,220
But I thought you knew
that's just how I communicate.

640
00:52:26,180 --> 00:52:28,600
It was never because
I didn't consider you a friend.

641
00:52:32,640 --> 00:52:33,520
I know that.

642
00:52:36,190 --> 00:52:37,770
And I didn't act any better.

643
00:52:39,110 --> 00:52:40,730
Kinda embarrassing, actually.

644
00:52:42,740 --> 00:52:45,490
I feel like we've been best friends
for next to forever,

645
00:52:46,110 --> 00:52:47,160
but I only just got it.

646
00:52:47,990 --> 00:52:48,830
What?

647
00:52:48,910 --> 00:52:52,410
You're not cold naturally,
but you just pretend like you are.

648
00:52:55,330 --> 00:52:57,880
And it was just a way for you
to protect yourself.

649
00:53:06,930 --> 00:53:08,180
I'll wait for you, okay?

650
00:53:16,020 --> 00:53:17,190
Please hurry back.

651
00:53:22,730 --> 00:53:24,280
My friend, Jung Jae-i.

652
00:53:27,820 --> 00:53:29,160
Take care of yourself,

653
00:53:30,240 --> 00:53:31,330
my mean…

654
00:53:33,330 --> 00:53:34,790
and beautiful friend.

655
00:53:40,340 --> 00:53:41,380
Let's go.

656
00:54:05,320 --> 00:54:06,440
Could you pull over?

657
00:54:18,500 --> 00:54:20,170
Skip school and spend the day with me.

658
00:54:28,680 --> 00:54:30,340
-You have to hold on, okay?
-Okay.

659
00:54:30,430 --> 00:54:32,850
-All right?
-I'll hold on. Now, let's ride.

660
00:54:34,060 --> 00:54:35,680
-Ooh!
-So close.

661
00:54:35,770 --> 00:54:37,480
-Are you good?
-Let me try again.

662
00:54:38,440 --> 00:54:39,560
-I'm going.
-Let's go.

663
00:54:43,020 --> 00:54:46,110
-Look at me. How am I doing?
-That's it. Try coming this way.

664
00:54:55,120 --> 00:54:57,080
-Whoa!
-Easier than I thought it'd be!

665
00:54:59,710 --> 00:55:01,920
-You're good at this. You are.
-I know, right?

666
00:55:03,960 --> 00:55:06,090
What do you think? I'm good, aren't I?

667
00:55:09,170 --> 00:55:10,590
Here. Try it.

668
00:55:12,680 --> 00:55:14,760
Oh. This is… what?

669
00:55:15,640 --> 00:55:16,470
Toast.

670
00:55:19,770 --> 00:55:21,140
Just try it, all right?

671
00:55:21,980 --> 00:55:24,270
Hold on. When did you try this before?

672
00:55:25,860 --> 00:55:27,320
I actually haven't yet.

673
00:55:28,030 --> 00:55:29,570
I wanted to try it with you.

674
00:55:38,330 --> 00:55:39,540
Ooh, it's really good.

675
00:55:39,620 --> 00:55:41,080
-Quick. Try it.
-Let's go.

676
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:48,170
How is it?

677
00:55:48,250 --> 00:55:50,050
-Mmm. Really good.
-It's good, isn't it?

678
00:55:51,340 --> 00:55:54,050
Does this chef have a Michelin star?
They should be famous!

679
00:55:54,550 --> 00:55:57,350
-You're not hungry? I'm taking yours too!
-No! No way, I'm gonna eat it.

680
00:55:57,430 --> 00:55:58,770
Let's get another one.

681
00:56:09,980 --> 00:56:11,490
The weather is beautiful.

682
00:56:12,070 --> 00:56:13,240
The breeze feels good too.

683
00:56:14,200 --> 00:56:15,200
Yeah, real good.

684
00:56:16,370 --> 00:56:17,240
Ri-an.

685
00:56:18,330 --> 00:56:20,250
Kang Ha once said to me

686
00:56:21,870 --> 00:56:23,580
that I should find and protect

687
00:56:24,210 --> 00:56:26,540
whatever makes me happiest in life.

688
00:56:27,710 --> 00:56:29,420
So I thought about it.

689
00:56:31,970 --> 00:56:33,220
And it's you, Ri-an.

690
00:56:34,930 --> 00:56:37,850
From the moment I first saw you
when we were children,

691
00:56:38,600 --> 00:56:40,720
you have always been part of my world.

692
00:56:41,430 --> 00:56:44,230
That's how I survived and still survive.

693
00:56:44,730 --> 00:56:46,860
Even to the 18-year-old Jung Jae-i,

694
00:56:46,940 --> 00:56:50,480
you are her one and only source of light.

695
00:56:57,030 --> 00:56:58,160
You're mine as well.

696
00:56:58,950 --> 00:57:02,370
If it wasn't for you,
I wouldn't be here either. No way.

697
00:57:10,130 --> 00:57:11,420
But, Ri-an,

698
00:57:12,550 --> 00:57:14,470
I think it's probably time

699
00:57:16,130 --> 00:57:17,590
to stop being so dependent.

700
00:57:20,140 --> 00:57:22,600
I'm looking forward to us meeting again

701
00:57:23,350 --> 00:57:25,980
when we no longer have
to lean on each other

702
00:57:26,060 --> 00:57:28,810
but can share
in each other's happiness individually.

703
00:57:29,730 --> 00:57:31,610
Then we can come back together.

704
00:57:34,030 --> 00:57:36,030
Let's say goodbye with a smile

705
00:57:36,610 --> 00:57:38,620
so that one day we can be together

706
00:57:40,160 --> 00:57:41,490
and smile again.

707
00:57:56,220 --> 00:57:57,760
Jae-i, I hope that…

708
00:58:00,850 --> 00:58:02,640
you don't have such a hard time.

709
00:58:04,680 --> 00:58:07,390
I only want you to be happy, Jae-i.

710
00:58:22,120 --> 00:58:23,120
Me too.

711
00:58:25,660 --> 00:58:27,120
I also hope that…

712
00:58:32,420 --> 00:58:35,260
you always smile
and lead a beautiful life.

713
00:59:50,160 --> 00:59:52,250
Moving forward in time,

714
00:59:52,330 --> 00:59:56,500
we'll discover the poetic verses
of William Shakespeare

715
00:59:56,590 --> 00:59:57,880
and delve into the…

716
00:59:57,960 --> 01:00:00,470
When you substitute it for five,
it becomes minus two here.

717
01:00:00,550 --> 01:00:02,130
-Do you follow me?
-Right.

718
01:00:03,220 --> 01:00:05,680
Hey, this looks nice.
Did your mom buy this for you?

719
01:00:05,760 --> 01:00:07,850
-Two, three. One, two.
-Hey, give me that.

720
01:00:09,350 --> 01:00:12,310
I'll be graduating, so I won't be able
to take care of you like I have been.

721
01:00:12,390 --> 01:00:14,150
You'll take care of everyone now.

722
01:00:14,230 --> 01:00:16,770
Did you get me a gift for graduation?
I'm just…

723
01:00:16,860 --> 01:00:18,860
Get off your damn phone!
A senior's talking!

724
01:00:18,940 --> 01:00:20,320
Ugh, jeez.

725
01:00:21,030 --> 01:00:22,030
Hey!

726
01:00:55,480 --> 01:00:56,730
Jae-i said, "Say sorry."

727
01:00:57,440 --> 01:00:59,070
Um, is it for--

728
01:00:59,150 --> 01:01:00,440
I mean, who else is here?

729
01:01:04,360 --> 01:01:05,860
This isn't like you, He-ra.

730
01:01:08,570 --> 01:01:10,700
I was wondering
who'd eat this kinda thing.

731
01:01:11,240 --> 01:01:12,620
I heard you introduced her to it.

732
01:01:14,710 --> 01:01:15,540
Well,

733
01:01:16,620 --> 01:01:19,210
she didn't actually eat it,
so she wouldn't know if it was good.

734
01:01:23,090 --> 01:01:24,340
Too sweet.

735
01:01:24,420 --> 01:01:25,470
Whoa!

736
01:01:25,550 --> 01:01:26,510
Who is this for?

737
01:01:26,590 --> 01:01:27,890
Ugh.

738
01:02:25,230 --> 01:02:27,110
I didn't know
it would turn out this way.

739
01:02:27,200 --> 01:02:29,990
I tried so many times to stop
and forget everything.

740
01:02:32,070 --> 01:02:32,990
I just…

741
01:02:34,330 --> 01:02:35,580
I just wanted…

742
01:02:36,200 --> 01:02:37,870
I just wanted to be with you.

743
01:02:40,040 --> 01:02:41,040
But I couldn't.

744
01:02:41,790 --> 01:02:42,920
I wasn't able.

745
01:02:44,590 --> 01:02:46,800
I couldn't let
another tragedy happen again.

746
01:02:47,760 --> 01:02:49,090
It's why I was here.

747
01:02:51,510 --> 01:02:52,350
Kang Ha.

748
01:02:52,430 --> 01:02:54,100
So I had no other options.

749
01:02:56,470 --> 01:02:58,310
I didn't know it would force you to go.

750
01:03:00,600 --> 01:03:01,520
Sorry.

751
01:03:04,230 --> 01:03:06,030
I'm sorry for making you leave.

752
01:03:07,530 --> 01:03:09,450
I'm sorry for having a crush on you

753
01:03:10,070 --> 01:03:11,530
and for everything.

754
01:03:20,960 --> 01:03:23,080
You said you wanted to see me smile.

755
01:03:24,210 --> 01:03:26,710
You won't be able to see it
through those tears.

756
01:03:33,260 --> 01:03:34,680
Don't worry too much.

757
01:03:36,470 --> 01:03:37,640
I'm not going.

758
01:03:38,890 --> 01:03:39,810
You're not?

759
01:03:41,770 --> 01:03:44,730
I'm gonna stand on my own
and follow my heart.

760
01:03:47,610 --> 01:03:51,110
I'm going to a new place to start over
where I'll be happy.

761
01:03:54,990 --> 01:03:57,160
So, Kang Ha…

762
01:03:59,620 --> 01:04:01,210
don't worry about me at all

763
01:04:03,000 --> 01:04:04,000
and take care.

764
01:04:15,760 --> 01:04:16,680
Oh yeah.

765
01:04:17,930 --> 01:04:18,930
That day.

766
01:04:19,890 --> 01:04:22,440
Do you remember
the last question you asked?

767
01:04:33,400 --> 01:04:34,610
You were right about it.

768
01:04:35,110 --> 01:04:36,160
I was lying to you.

769
01:07:04,350 --> 01:07:05,390
Hi, Mom.

770
01:12:15,070 --> 01:12:16,660
YOU LOOK SHAKEN UP, KIM RI-AN